1
00:00:15,033 --> 00:00:17,600
Don't be scared, girl.
Respect your elders.

2
00:00:17,733 --> 00:00:19,700
Wow! Wow! Wow!

3
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:21,100
Elders?

4
00:00:21,233 --> 00:00:23,033
We're not even seniors yet!

5
00:00:23,167 --> 00:00:25,467
- We're forever young!
- What?

6
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:26,967
Sorry to bother you.

7
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:28,300
Hey, no! It's fine.

8
00:00:28,433 --> 00:00:30,867
I just really want
to talk to my sister.

9
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:33,167
Don't worry,
I know where she is.

10
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:35,167
It's easy for us
to find people.

11
00:00:36,433 --> 00:00:38,767
You can really find someone
wherever they are? !

12
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:40,567
Yes, wherever they are!

13
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:42,667
Alright, I'll help you
with your sister.

14
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:44,300
If you help me find my ex.

15
00:00:44,433 --> 00:00:46,467
I'm starting to worry,
you know.

16
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:49,833
Sometimes you're just quiet
and spaced out.

17
00:00:49,967 --> 00:00:52,400
Is that all
because of that jerk?

18
00:00:52,533 --> 00:00:54,100
Grandma...

19
00:00:54,233 --> 00:00:56,833
I still love that jerk.

20
00:00:56,967 --> 00:00:58,500
[SCOFFS]

21
00:00:58,633 --> 00:01:01,767
That's just the ghost
of what you used to feel.

22
00:01:01,900 --> 00:01:04,300
- Oh!
- Whoa! Very Gen Z-like.

23
00:01:04,433 --> 00:01:05,633
I know!

24
00:01:05,767 --> 00:01:07,200
Let's pretend you're Vhal.

25
00:01:07,367 --> 00:01:09,800
- A-As you will.
- Come.

26
00:01:09,933 --> 00:01:11,500
Why did you ghost me?

27
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:20,333
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

28
00:01:20,467 --> 00:01:21,800
I love you.

29
00:01:26,033 --> 00:01:28,400
And I can't live without you.

30
00:01:31,733 --> 00:01:33,667
- I can't li--
- Vhal...

31
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:40,667
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

32
00:01:45,167 --> 00:01:47,367
Oh, uh...

33
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:49,800
[CLAPS] So, how was it?
Was that good?

34
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:52,333
I even made myself cry.

35
00:01:52,467 --> 00:01:54,767
- Well?
- Uh... It was good.

36
00:01:54,900 --> 00:01:57,000
- Mmm?
- You did good.

37
00:01:57,133 --> 00:01:59,267
- I almost cried myself.
- [SNIFFS]

38
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:02,200
I'm sure he will
appreciate your words.

39
00:02:02,333 --> 00:02:05,267
[SQUEALS] I'm so excited.

40
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:09,567
Oh, I should stop crying
before my eyes get puffy.

41
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:12,500
Phew... I'm so excited.

42
00:02:12,633 --> 00:02:19,233
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

43
00:02:19,967 --> 00:02:26,800
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

44
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,400
- Oh, come on.
- I know, right?

45
00:02:57,533 --> 00:03:00,367
This is where I found him.
At this vacation house.

46
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:03,900
And there...
in that room...

47
00:03:04,033 --> 00:03:05,200
is where that
person is staying.

48
00:03:05,900 --> 00:03:09,433
[EXHALES SHARPLY] So, bestie?
How do I look?

49
00:03:09,567 --> 00:03:11,433
You look really beautiful,
girly pop.

50
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:13,467
You're more than
ready for this.

51
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:15,067
Thank you, Treb.

52
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,700
Are you sure of what
you're about to do?

53
00:03:16,833 --> 00:03:17,900
Yes, I'm very sure.

54
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:20,733
Then why do you
look like you're shaking?

55
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:24,633
I'm a bit nervous,
but I'm okay. I'm okay.

56
00:03:24,767 --> 00:03:29,000
It's now or never.
Right? Come on.

57
00:03:29,133 --> 00:03:31,000
Wait. Hold on, girl.

58
00:03:31,133 --> 00:03:33,967
Uh... Are you
prepared to discover

59
00:03:34,100 --> 00:03:36,200
why you were ghosted by Vhal?

60
00:03:36,333 --> 00:03:37,667
You worry too much.

61
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:40,400
- But the picture could be--
- Hey, stop it.

62
00:03:40,533 --> 00:03:42,833
Like I told you, it was
probably sent by a hater.

63
00:03:42,967 --> 00:03:46,433
They could've sent similar
nonsense to him. Right?

64
00:03:46,567 --> 00:03:50,500
So, it's better for us to meet
and find out the truth. Hmm?

65
00:03:50,633 --> 00:03:52,867
- But it's just--
- Girl, shush.

66
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,267
Shush, shush, shush.

67
00:03:54,433 --> 00:03:56,133
- Shush, shush, shush, shush.
- Shush, shush.

68
00:03:56,267 --> 00:03:57,967
- Shush, okay?
- This guy's noisier.

69
00:03:58,100 --> 00:03:59,200
- Just shush.
- You shush.

70
00:03:59,333 --> 00:04:01,100
Okay, how about this?

71
00:04:01,233 --> 00:04:03,233
I'll look through
the window first.

72
00:04:03,367 --> 00:04:06,967
And if the coast
is clear, I'll knock.

73
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:11,700
If it isn't, then I'll stop
being obsessed with him. Okay?

74
00:04:11,833 --> 00:04:14,200
- Let's go. [GIGGLES]
- Okay, fine.

75
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:19,467
Oh, keep quiet, okay?
Oh, right. You're ghosts.

76
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,600
It's us who should
keep quiet, girl.

77
00:04:25,033 --> 00:04:26,200
Girl...

78
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,600
Bestie...

79
00:04:28,767 --> 00:04:29,867
There's Vhal.

80
00:04:31,767 --> 00:04:35,400
He looks heartbroken too.
Should I go talk to him?

81
00:04:38,067 --> 00:04:39,967
[WOMAN] I finished changing.

82
00:04:40,100 --> 00:04:41,600
[GASPS]

83
00:04:43,667 --> 00:04:45,300
- Uh...
- What is it?

84
00:04:45,433 --> 00:04:47,933
Um, it's nothing, girl.
I think we should go.

85
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:50,300
Girl--

86
00:04:51,100 --> 00:04:52,467
[WOMAN] Come on, come on.

87
00:04:55,500 --> 00:05:02,533
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

88
00:05:06,167 --> 00:05:08,667
- Jaja...
- I'm okay.

89
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,567
Seems like Jaja's not
in a good mood right now.

90
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:13,000
I think she needs
Grandpa Wilberto's support.

91
00:05:13,133 --> 00:05:15,267
- Hey, go to her.
- [SIGHS]

92
00:05:23,467 --> 00:05:26,033
[SNIFFLES, SOBS]

93
00:05:27,433 --> 00:05:29,100
- Don't cry.
- [SCREAMS IN SURPRISE]

94
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:32,600
You almost gave me
a heart attack!

95
00:05:32,733 --> 00:05:33,733
[SOBBING SOFTLY]

96
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:36,333
You shouldn't waste
your tears on that guy.

97
00:05:36,467 --> 00:05:38,367
- [SOBBING]
- Look at that...

98
00:05:39,233 --> 00:05:41,100
Even the rain
shares your tears.

99
00:05:41,233 --> 00:05:42,267
[SNIFFLES]

100
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:45,900
Did you know that
he's with someone?

101
00:05:46,733 --> 00:05:47,700
[HICCUPS]

102
00:05:52,967 --> 00:05:54,767
[SNIFFLES]

103
00:05:56,067 --> 00:05:57,433
- Jaja...
- [SNIFFLES]

104
00:05:58,533 --> 00:06:01,733
If he really loves you,
he wouldn't make you cry.

105
00:06:02,433 --> 00:06:03,567
[SNIFFLES]

106
00:06:04,533 --> 00:06:07,300
[SCOFFS, SNIFFLES]

107
00:06:07,467 --> 00:06:10,333
Maybe I don't
deserve his love.

108
00:06:11,067 --> 00:06:13,467
Maybe I'm in the wrong.

109
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:15,000
- Don't say that.
- [SOBBING]

110
00:06:15,133 --> 00:06:17,700
Why do they always leave me?

111
00:06:18,333 --> 00:06:20,100
Daddy...

112
00:06:20,233 --> 00:06:21,600
Vhal...

113
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:23,733
[SNIFFS TEARILY]

114
00:06:23,867 --> 00:06:25,067
All of them...

115
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:29,100
They all left me
like I was nothing.

116
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:32,433
Like I don't deserve
to be loved.

117
00:06:33,967 --> 00:06:37,467
[SOBBING, CRYING]

118
00:06:39,167 --> 00:06:43,567
[SNIFFLES, SOBBING]

119
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:47,400
[SOBBING]

120
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,467
[SNIFFLES, SOBBING]

121
00:06:54,600 --> 00:07:01,633
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

122
00:07:10,533 --> 00:07:12,067
There's nothing
wrong with you.

123
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:16,133
They're in the wrong
for leaving you.

124
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:18,767
For abandoning you.

125
00:07:22,367 --> 00:07:23,567
I'm just like them.

126
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:30,767
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

127
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:39,133
["KINAKABAHAN" BY LILY
PLAYING]

128
00:07:50,367 --> 00:07:51,600
Let's go home.

129
00:07:51,733 --> 00:07:55,967
[GRAVEL CRUNCHING]

130
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:57,100
[SIGHS]

131
00:08:05,233 --> 00:08:09,267
Uh... So, yeah...
Thanks for the help, you two.

132
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:11,833
Looks like my friend here
needs to rest.

133
00:08:11,967 --> 00:08:14,533
- Good night.
- Night, girls.

134
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,100
Treb.

135
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:44,500
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

136
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:55,933
["TAYO HANGGANG DULO" BY FYANG
SMITH AND JM IBARRA PLAYING]

137
00:09:10,933 --> 00:09:17,967
["TAYO HANGGANG DULO" CONTINUES]

138
00:09:32,933 --> 00:09:36,467
["TAYO HANGGANG DULO" CONTINUES]

139
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:40,000
Thank you
for being there for me.

140
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:48,167
["TAYO HANGGANG DULO"
INSTRUMENTAL PLAYING]

141
00:10:04,367 --> 00:10:05,633
Man...

142
00:10:10,367 --> 00:10:12,667
Man, what are you doing?
Are you a security guard?

143
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:14,933
Are we really going to
keep watch here all night?

144
00:10:16,867 --> 00:10:19,033
- You're worried, huh?
- [SIGHS]

145
00:10:20,833 --> 00:10:22,000
I think Jaja was really hurt

146
00:10:22,133 --> 00:10:23,767
by what that person
did to her.

147
00:10:24,433 --> 00:10:25,900
Of course, she was, man.

148
00:10:26,033 --> 00:10:27,333
How would you feel if
someone left you hanging

149
00:10:27,467 --> 00:10:28,767
and started dating
someone else?

150
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:31,667
Ouch!
That would seriously hurt.

151
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:36,900
Ooh... Someone's concerned.

152
00:10:38,567 --> 00:10:40,167
I- I just thought...

153
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:44,600
Did Nadia feel
the same back then?

154
00:10:45,333 --> 00:10:47,000
You know, when I was gone.

155
00:10:48,433 --> 00:10:50,233
It's like I just
left her suddenly.

156
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:52,833
Don't worry, man.

157
00:10:52,967 --> 00:10:54,867
Now, you've finished
your deal with Jaja.

158
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,967
You and Nadia
can patch things up.

159
00:10:57,100 --> 00:11:00,333
But the problem is...
if she's okay.

160
00:11:01,833 --> 00:11:03,300
Jaja's brave.

161
00:11:04,667 --> 00:11:06,000
She's strong.

162
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:10,100
I believe she will be fine.

163
00:11:10,233 --> 00:11:11,500
But what if she isn't?

164
00:11:11,633 --> 00:11:13,100
What if she never
leaves the house?

165
00:11:13,233 --> 00:11:14,100
What if she gets hungry?

166
00:11:14,233 --> 00:11:16,167
- What if--
- What if you shut up?

167
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:20,367
All I'm saying is, man...

168
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:22,767
We should help her move on.

169
00:11:22,900 --> 00:11:25,500
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

170
00:11:25,633 --> 00:11:28,067
- Move on?
- Yeah.

171
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,933
So she can forget
about that pretty boy

172
00:11:30,067 --> 00:11:31,900
and return to her
bubbly personality.

173
00:11:32,033 --> 00:11:33,300
Everyone will be happy, right?

174
00:11:33,433 --> 00:11:34,467
[CHUCKLING]

175
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:36,133
I'm so good.
I just thought of that.

176
00:11:36,267 --> 00:11:38,767
[CHUCKLING]
Right?

177
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:40,867
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

178
00:11:43,367 --> 00:11:48,233
Girlie Pop, do you... want to
talk about what happened?

179
00:11:49,433 --> 00:11:51,333
I'm okay.

180
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:57,600
Hey, what do you
want to do tomorrow?

181
00:11:57,733 --> 00:12:01,267
Tell me. I'm game
for anything, I swear.

182
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:04,100
If you want, we can bring
that cute ghost of yours.

183
00:12:04,233 --> 00:12:05,833
[APPARITION SOUND]
Who's cute? Me?

184
00:12:06,533 --> 00:12:08,067
Yuck. No.

185
00:12:09,067 --> 00:12:10,533
- Ah...
- [WOOD CREAKING]

186
00:12:10,667 --> 00:12:12,900
- [SHUFFLING AROUND]
- [FOOTSTEPS]

187
00:12:13,033 --> 00:12:16,000
Girlie Pop, sorry
I let these two inside.

188
00:12:16,167 --> 00:12:18,633
I saw them out
in the garden, waiting.

189
00:12:18,767 --> 00:12:20,267
This way, you have
someone to talk to.

190
00:12:20,933 --> 00:12:22,600
Hey, um, uh...

191
00:12:22,733 --> 00:12:25,467
I invited Jaja to go
sight-seeing tomorrow.

192
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:27,000
- Mm.
- You know...

193
00:12:27,133 --> 00:12:30,933
To, uh... To help distract her
from... you know... from Vhal.

194
00:12:31,067 --> 00:12:33,267
Oh, that sounds
like a good plan.

195
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:34,767
Right, Treb?

196
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:35,967
I don't feel like going out.

197
00:12:36,100 --> 00:12:38,367
Besides...
the weather's too hot.

198
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:40,367
- [TRINKETS JINGLE]
- Uh...

199
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:45,300
Girly pop, isn't it hotter
when covered in your blanket?

200
00:12:46,433 --> 00:12:49,733
[WHISPERS] Hey, suggest
something we can do.

201
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:54,833
Hey, hey, hey!
What are you doing?

202
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,100
Psst, hey.

203
00:12:57,233 --> 00:12:59,333
My friend is safe.
He's a good boy.

204
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:04,133
All right.

205
00:13:05,267 --> 00:13:06,500
Okay.

206
00:13:09,933 --> 00:13:16,233
[GHOSTLY NOISE]

207
00:13:16,367 --> 00:13:23,233
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

208
00:13:32,167 --> 00:13:34,167
Wait, what are you
doing in my bed?

209
00:13:35,167 --> 00:13:38,733
So you don't get too hot.
I'm cold, remember?

210
00:13:38,867 --> 00:13:45,367
[ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

211
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:46,867
[PHONE CHIMES]

212
00:13:52,967 --> 00:13:55,300
Why are you always
on your phone?

213
00:13:56,133 --> 00:13:58,067
So that I always
stay updated.

214
00:13:59,533 --> 00:14:01,867
- What?
- Updated.

215
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,700
You know, on my
family, my friends,

216
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:06,933
my followers,
even the whole country.

217
00:14:07,833 --> 00:14:10,633
This is also where
I get the news.

218
00:14:10,767 --> 00:14:12,433
The news...

219
00:14:12,567 --> 00:14:14,033
There are newspapers, right?

220
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:18,100
You can read
newspapers online.

221
00:14:18,233 --> 00:14:20,600
Why not read them
in the morning?

222
00:14:20,733 --> 00:14:22,767
Then I'll be late
on the latest news.

223
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:25,000
Do you always have to be
first on the latest news?

224
00:14:25,133 --> 00:14:27,833
Put down your phone
and get some rest.

225
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:30,633
- [SIGHS]
- Back then,

226
00:14:30,767 --> 00:14:33,467
we lived without
telephones like that.

227
00:14:34,633 --> 00:14:35,867
It was all right.

228
00:14:37,033 --> 00:14:38,233
It was quiet.

229
00:14:38,967 --> 00:14:40,133
It was peaceful.

230
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:43,167
That was back then.

231
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:45,433
Things are different
these days.

232
00:14:45,567 --> 00:14:48,133
This is also a form
of entertainment for us.

233
00:14:48,267 --> 00:14:50,867
Hey! Entertainment?
A fun activity?

234
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,533
I got you, man.

235
00:14:52,667 --> 00:14:54,500
What do you want to do? Huh?

236
00:14:54,633 --> 00:14:55,900
Do you want to go to a disco?

237
00:14:56,033 --> 00:14:58,733
Anything you want,
I'll make it happen.

238
00:14:58,867 --> 00:15:00,833
You can move like this...
Sideways...

239
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:04,100
- Or like thi--
- Tsk, what are you doing?

240
00:15:04,233 --> 00:15:06,467
What? Those are steps
we did at the disco.

241
00:15:08,267 --> 00:15:10,300
- Hmph...
- You move like this...

242
00:15:10,433 --> 00:15:17,433
["CLINGY AF" BY FYANG SMITH
PLAYING]

243
00:15:22,067 --> 00:15:23,867
- [RUSHING WATER]
- You want to go swimming,

244
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:26,333
but we can't even swim.

245
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:29,133
What matters is you
cheer Jaja up, right?

246
00:15:30,833 --> 00:15:33,733
Well, here you go.
A swimming party.

247
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:35,300
We used to do this
all the time.

248
00:15:35,467 --> 00:15:38,333
[CHUCKLING]

249
00:15:38,467 --> 00:15:40,700
Oh! They're here!

250
00:15:40,833 --> 00:15:41,800
- Ja-- Jaja.
- Hi, girls!

251
00:15:41,933 --> 00:15:44,233
Treb! Tony! We're here!

252
00:15:44,367 --> 00:15:46,600
Oh, girly pop, you need this.
This is it.

253
00:15:46,733 --> 00:15:47,900
- Are you ready?
- Nice.

254
00:15:48,033 --> 00:15:49,733
- Are you good? All right.
- This place is nice.

255
00:15:49,867 --> 00:15:51,333
You know, I never
thought of doing this

256
00:15:51,467 --> 00:15:53,367
even though we always
meet up by the river.

257
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:55,567
- We should've swam before.
- It was Tony's idea.

258
00:15:55,700 --> 00:15:57,500
- You brought a lot of stuff.
- Well, at least...

259
00:15:57,633 --> 00:15:59,333
- ...you're still useful.
- Of course, I am.

260
00:15:59,467 --> 00:16:01,333
- Hey, be careful.
- Watch your step.

261
00:16:01,467 --> 00:16:03,267
Hey, you're a ghost.
Don't be crazy.

262
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:04,933
Dude, did you forget
about being a ghost?

263
00:16:05,067 --> 00:16:07,100
Girly pop, are you ready?

264
00:16:07,233 --> 00:16:09,567
- Let's take photos.
- Sure, sure. Let's go.

265
00:16:09,733 --> 00:16:11,900
- We need lots of selfies.
- We'll take tons of photos.

266
00:16:12,033 --> 00:16:14,567
- That spot's perfect.
- Oh, yes!

267
00:16:16,067 --> 00:16:17,633
Did you bring food with you?

268
00:16:17,767 --> 00:16:19,700
- Food? Why?
- Jaja.

269
00:16:21,067 --> 00:16:23,400
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, thanks for asking.

270
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:26,100
Bestie!

271
00:16:26,233 --> 00:16:28,267
- It's selfie time!
- I miss trips like this.

272
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:30,633
Let's start taking selfies!

273
00:16:32,367 --> 00:16:36,767
- [PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING]
- [SURPRISED NOISES]

274
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:38,767
- Wait, hold on...
- Ooh! Wait- No, dude.

275
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:40,133
Let them be.

276
00:16:40,267 --> 00:16:42,367
- [TONY GIGGLING]
- Okay!

277
00:16:42,533 --> 00:16:44,867
- Selfie! This is it, girl!
- We must've gone to heaven.

278
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,467
We've crossed over, man.

279
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:48,800
Hey, put-- Put on some...

280
00:16:48,933 --> 00:16:52,133
You should cover...
Cover yourselves up.

281
00:16:53,533 --> 00:16:55,033
Cover ourselves up?

282
00:16:55,167 --> 00:16:56,267
Oh, come on, Treb.

283
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:59,067
- You act as if we're naked.
- [GIGGLES]

284
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:01,833
This is what we wear
when we go swimming.

285
00:17:01,967 --> 00:17:03,567
Yes. These are
called swimsuits.

286
00:17:03,700 --> 00:17:06,867
You know, this makes him
sound more of a boomer, right?

287
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:10,233
Oh, for real, bestie.
Like I told you...

288
00:17:10,367 --> 00:17:13,967
This will reveal how old
Grandpa Wilberto is.

289
00:17:14,100 --> 00:17:16,067
It really shows
how old you are.

290
00:17:16,233 --> 00:17:17,200
Don't mind them.

291
00:17:17,333 --> 00:17:18,633
Let's keep taking
selfies, bestie.

292
00:17:18,767 --> 00:17:19,767
Okay. Get ready...

293
00:17:21,467 --> 00:17:23,667
W-Wait, hold on!

294
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:25,300
Emma, erase that!

295
00:17:25,433 --> 00:17:27,467
- Why should I?
- What? Why?

296
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:29,067
It doesn't look good.

297
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:31,967
Seriously? You think
I'm ugly too?

298
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:34,267
Jaja, I didn't mean you.
It's your clothes.

299
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:37,000
Could you please not judge me?

300
00:17:38,567 --> 00:17:39,333
I need this.

301
00:17:39,467 --> 00:17:41,767
My followers need
to see that I'm okay

302
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:43,800
and I'm not depressed.

303
00:17:43,933 --> 00:17:45,500
Because right now?

304
00:17:45,633 --> 00:17:48,033
I feel so ugly.

305
00:17:48,967 --> 00:17:50,667
I just need...

306
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:54,800
just a bit of affirmation
that I'm still beautiful

307
00:17:54,933 --> 00:17:57,367
and that I'm not
that easy to replace.

308
00:17:58,733 --> 00:18:02,200
So, could you please
just let me have this?

309
00:18:02,333 --> 00:18:04,033
Jaja, you are irreplaceable.

310
00:18:04,167 --> 00:18:06,133
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

311
00:18:06,267 --> 00:18:08,433
If someone sees you as such,
then they're blind.

312
00:18:09,933 --> 00:18:12,100
Because they don't see
your true worth.

313
00:18:12,233 --> 00:18:19,267
["PRINSESA" BY KENANIAH PLAYING]

314
00:18:28,167 --> 00:18:29,367
You know what?

315
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:31,433
Even though there's nothing
wrong with our outfits...

316
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:36,467
Fine. We'll cover up, okay?

317
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:38,333
Bestie, let's
put on more clothes.

318
00:18:38,467 --> 00:18:40,567
- Just one picture, please?
- We'll take just one more.

319
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:41,567
We won't post it!

320
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:43,167
Something for us
to remember this day.

321
00:18:43,300 --> 00:18:44,633
We even dressed up for this.

322
00:18:44,767 --> 00:18:45,700
You're right.

323
00:18:48,633 --> 00:18:50,467
You were a bit
intense earlier, man.

324
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:52,400
We came here to have
fun and enjoy, right?

325
00:18:52,533 --> 00:18:53,700
[JAJA] We're done taking photos.

326
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:55,833
- We're covering up now.
- See? More clothes.

327
00:18:57,300 --> 00:19:00,233
Look at what you've done.
What a shame.

328
00:19:00,367 --> 00:19:03,100
["PRINSESA" CONTINUES]

329
00:19:03,233 --> 00:19:05,233
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

330
00:19:06,167 --> 00:19:08,133
Do you hear me?

331
00:19:08,267 --> 00:19:15,267
- [GIGGLING]
- ["PRINSESA" CONTINUES]

332
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:17,500
It's cold!

333
00:19:17,633 --> 00:19:18,667
[BREATH QUIVERS]

334
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:21,267
This is so fun!

335
00:19:22,667 --> 00:19:24,200
[SONG ENDS]

336
00:19:24,333 --> 00:19:28,567
Bestie, is Treb a friendly
ghost or something else?

337
00:19:28,733 --> 00:19:30,700
Is he really going
to do that all day?

338
00:19:30,833 --> 00:19:32,133
[JAJA] I don't know.

339
00:19:32,267 --> 00:19:33,867
[EMMA] Oh! [LAUGHS]

340
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,600
And look at Tony.

341
00:19:35,733 --> 00:19:39,433
He may look stupid, but at
least he's enjoying himself.

342
00:19:39,567 --> 00:19:41,967
[LAUGHING]

343
00:19:42,100 --> 00:19:43,867
Hey, Treb!

344
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,467
Hey, Treb!

345
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:48,833
- What?
- You can relax if you want to!

346
00:19:48,967 --> 00:19:51,900
Um... I'd rather keep watch.

347
00:19:52,033 --> 00:19:53,800
We don't really
know these parts.

348
00:19:53,933 --> 00:19:57,467
Some bandidos might show up.
You might get hurt.

349
00:19:57,600 --> 00:19:59,400
Bandidos , bestie?
What are those?

350
00:19:59,533 --> 00:20:01,600
I was probably absent
when we studied those.

351
00:20:01,767 --> 00:20:06,067
Seriously, girlie pop?
Bandidos mean bad people.

352
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:07,433
Ohh, so that's what
that means.

353
00:20:07,567 --> 00:20:08,900
- Yes.
- You studied that?

354
00:20:09,033 --> 00:20:10,233
But you have to admit,

355
00:20:10,367 --> 00:20:13,433
Grandpa Wilberto's a good
knight in shining armor.

356
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:15,367
You know, girlie pop...

357
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:18,367
Maybe if you
were his girlfriend,

358
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:20,767
he would take care
of you well.

359
00:20:20,900 --> 00:20:22,667
What do you think?

360
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:29,033
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

361
00:20:29,167 --> 00:20:30,867
Wilberto!

362
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,200
Come here.

363
00:20:34,133 --> 00:20:36,767
We've been friends
for five decades, man,

364
00:20:36,933 --> 00:20:39,233
but this is the first time
I've seen you like this.

365
00:20:40,600 --> 00:20:42,167
Like what?

366
00:20:42,300 --> 00:20:43,967
You're being cheesy.

367
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:45,467
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

368
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:47,400
- [JAJA] Bestie.
- [EMMA] Mm?

369
00:20:47,533 --> 00:20:49,267
- I'll swim a bit over there.
- Alright.

370
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:50,867
- I'll be right here.
- Okay.

371
00:20:52,567 --> 00:20:55,000
I just want
to make Jaja happy.

372
00:20:55,133 --> 00:20:57,467
Just like we've discussed.

373
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:59,333
I get what you mean, man.

374
00:20:59,467 --> 00:21:02,733
But you're putting so much
effort to make her happy.

375
00:21:03,767 --> 00:21:05,867
[WILBERTO] Isn't that
the right thing to do?

376
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:07,467
I'm just doing what's right.

377
00:21:10,300 --> 00:21:11,967
Just between the two of us...

378
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:14,367
But... is she your type?

379
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:20,900
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

380
00:21:21,033 --> 00:21:22,533
What are you talking about?

381
00:21:23,667 --> 00:21:25,533
This is about
helping her out, Tony.

382
00:21:26,367 --> 00:21:28,267
You suggested that
we do this, remember?

383
00:21:29,267 --> 00:21:31,033
To help her move on?

384
00:21:31,167 --> 00:21:35,167
Ahh... I get it now.
So, all of this,

385
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:37,700
even the part where
you make her happy,

386
00:21:37,833 --> 00:21:38,867
is all business?

387
00:21:40,133 --> 00:21:42,233
It's all just part
of your deal?

388
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:50,933
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

389
00:21:52,867 --> 00:21:54,067
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

390
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:55,967
Um...

391
00:21:56,100 --> 00:21:57,567
I'll just go take a break.

392
00:21:57,700 --> 00:21:59,967
You're such a cold--
I mean...

393
00:22:01,367 --> 00:22:02,867
I'm starting to get cold.

394
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:09,833
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

395
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:17,167
Don't think about it, girl.
Calm down.

396
00:22:17,333 --> 00:22:19,067
You had a deal, remember?

397
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:20,833
Were you expecting
something else?

398
00:22:22,133 --> 00:22:25,167
- [MUSIC FADES]
- [WATER RUSHING]

399
00:22:25,300 --> 00:22:27,433
Uh... I'll dip in again.

400
00:22:27,567 --> 00:22:28,767
I just grabbed something.

401
00:22:28,900 --> 00:22:29,800
Jaja.

402
00:22:33,633 --> 00:22:37,233
It's fine, Treb.
It's really fine.

403
00:22:37,367 --> 00:22:41,267
I know that we had a deal.

404
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:43,500
I'll hold up
my end of the deal.

405
00:22:43,633 --> 00:22:46,700
So, don't worry.
I won't leave you hanging.

406
00:22:46,833 --> 00:22:48,300
I know.

407
00:22:48,467 --> 00:22:50,667
But this isn't about that.

408
00:22:51,833 --> 00:22:53,900
That conversation you heard
between me and Tony...

409
00:22:54,033 --> 00:22:56,467
It's true that I want to mend
bridges with my sibling.

410
00:22:57,767 --> 00:22:59,900
You've known that
since the beginning, right?

411
00:23:01,467 --> 00:23:03,633
Yes, that's why
no hard feelings.

412
00:23:03,767 --> 00:23:05,867
I'm actually grateful because...

413
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:10,767
you've been care enough
to humor and entertain me.

414
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:14,600
So, don't worry.
I'm not mad. I promise.

415
00:23:15,500 --> 00:23:17,533
Then why can't you
look me in the eye?

416
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:21,533
Happy?

417
00:23:23,033 --> 00:23:26,733
Jaja, I didn't do all of that
just to fix things with Nadia.

418
00:23:26,867 --> 00:23:27,933
Then why?

419
00:23:29,133 --> 00:23:30,700
I just thought...

420
00:23:32,033 --> 00:23:35,767
If you could get over the
sadness that Vhal caused you,

421
00:23:37,067 --> 00:23:40,400
maybe Nadia can also get over
the sadness I've caused her.

422
00:23:42,733 --> 00:23:45,100
If you can be happy
without Vhal,

423
00:23:45,233 --> 00:23:47,533
maybe my sibling
can be happy too,

424
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:49,867
even though I'm gone now.

425
00:23:53,367 --> 00:23:56,467
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

426
00:23:56,633 --> 00:23:58,767
It's hard to forget.

427
00:24:03,300 --> 00:24:05,500
But you don't
have to forget him.

428
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:09,867
He became a part of your life.

429
00:24:10,933 --> 00:24:13,967
What matters is that
you don't limit your life

430
00:24:14,100 --> 00:24:15,433
because of him.

431
00:24:16,433 --> 00:24:18,667
Don't make him
the center of your life.

432
00:24:20,367 --> 00:24:22,800
Jaja, the world
is a big place.

433
00:24:22,933 --> 00:24:25,667
You will meet
a lot more people.

434
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:29,667
You will endure a lot more
hardships and happiness.

435
00:24:30,467 --> 00:24:32,500
But if you make Vhal
your world...

436
00:24:33,867 --> 00:24:35,833
You're closing yourself
to a lot of things.

437
00:24:35,967 --> 00:24:39,200
You're denying yourself
the chance to be happy.

438
00:24:42,733 --> 00:24:45,600
I don't know
if I could still be happy.

439
00:24:45,733 --> 00:24:47,667
Jaja, just open your eyes.

440
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:53,800
There are a lot
of people who love you.

441
00:24:53,933 --> 00:25:00,933
["MULTO" BY HEALY
AFTER DARK PLAYING"

442
00:25:22,300 --> 00:25:29,167
["MULTO" CONTINUES]

443
00:25:42,733 --> 00:25:44,833
I tried to protect her.

444
00:25:44,967 --> 00:25:49,567
"Unfortunately, like most
of our bravest heroes,

445
00:25:49,700 --> 00:25:53,433
there exist little documentation
of his heroic feats

446
00:25:53,567 --> 00:25:56,467
and how he defended
a small town

447
00:25:56,600 --> 00:25:58,400
until his death."

448
00:25:58,533 --> 00:26:01,667
So Wilberto was a hero.

449
00:26:01,800 --> 00:26:03,433
It's a sign of respect
to introduce your friends

450
00:26:03,567 --> 00:26:04,667
to you parents.

451
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:07,733
They'll be shocked
to learn you're a ghost!

452
00:26:07,867 --> 00:26:11,000
Ghost? Who are you
talking to?

453
00:26:11,167 --> 00:26:13,733
They might say
I'm crazy! [CHUCKLES]

454
00:26:13,867 --> 00:26:15,900
Seeing you smile
makes me happy.

455
00:26:16,033 --> 00:26:17,133
[GASPS]

456
00:26:17,267 --> 00:26:18,767
Guard your heart, okay?

457
00:26:18,900 --> 00:26:20,833
"Guard your heart"?!

458
00:26:20,967 --> 00:26:21,967
Excuse me?

459
00:26:22,100 --> 00:26:25,500
Girl, may I remind you,
Treb is a ghost.

460
00:26:25,633 --> 00:26:27,433
We have the option
to open her third eye.

461
00:26:27,567 --> 00:26:31,267
Emma and Jaja
at your service.

462
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:33,400
- [SLAMS]
- Wait!

463
00:26:33,533 --> 00:26:34,800
Are you okay?
